I had a hospital stay a few years ago after serious accident, and at
least a few of the treating physicians made inappropriate entries in my
medical records, ones that have seriously biased other physicians I've
visited since.  I'm also concerned because these records could
potentially impact the care I'll receive if I am hospitalized again.

What can I do?  The hospital has offered me the opportunity to enter a
statement in the record, explaining my position on the comments.
However, this doesn't seem terribly helpful, as the comments of an M.D.
always carry a great deal of weight, far more than those of a patient.

There are also some highly damaging remarks from two physicians at
family practice clinics. I have no idea what my rights are concerning
these records, and those clinics are not going to allow me to enter any
kind of statement.

What, if anything, can I do?  I don't want anyone to see these
records... ever. Any ideas would be appreciated.
