You can't control if the records are seen by another provider (or
billing) at the establishment where you say you had the misinformation
entered. You can, of course, refuse to permit other providers to see
those records by not signing a release of those records to the new
provider.

If you wish to expunge the record, that's another whole kettle of fish
and one not easily boiled. If so post back that you do.

Also if the information you say is erroneous demands disclosure, you
can't do anything about that disclosure. For example, I am mandated in
some of my work to report if I *suspect* child abuse or if I *suspect*
that there may be an act of violence.

Your post lacks sufficient detail to give a firm response.

