Whitewater,

You have sought medical care and treatment. As a part of this care you
were seen by physicians who made notes about their opinions of you, a
diagnosis, and a plan of treatment. These notes are a part of your medical
record. You feel that some of these opinions were "inappropriate" but offer
no explanation. You do indicate that several physicians have done this to
you. You have been offered the opportunity to record a statement explaining
your feelings about these opinions but you have rejected that. You ask for
advice.
You can always change doctors and hospitals. Inform the new physicians
that you wish them to start new records and forbid them to consult the old
records. It's possible that they will refuse your business. It's also
possible that the new physicians will reach the same opinions independently
thus putting you back to the beginning.
I don't see that you have a right to edit, delete, change, et c the
opinions of the experts whom you hired to give these opinions. It's possible
under some circumstances, I suppose, and if you have the money to waste you
may wish to consult an attorney.

Good luck,
Dave M.
