Just to play devil's advocate here...

Who says the remarks are "inappropriate"?  If you are not a medical
professional, you have no basis to say what should or should not be in
your medical record.  If you're not a doctor, you have no basis to say
that their opinions are incorrect.  You might have a basis to say that
events the doctors recorded transpired differently (or not at all), but
that doesn't let you delete the parts you disagree with.  It might give
you a basis to supplement the record, though.

BTW, what do you mean by "biased"?

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; What can I do?  The hospital has offered me the opportunity to enter a
