Um, how _can_ they do that, even if they want to?  Prevent you from
making a statement, that is?  Your "record" at that clinic should
include EVERYTHING they have in their files about you, and as a general
principle they should keep in your files everthing they GET from or
about you, including correspondence.  So, if you (or your attorney)
simply write them a letter stating your concerns, send it certified
mail so that YOU have a record it was received, and include language in
the letter asking that it be kept with your file, the clinic would have
to think long and hard about THEIR potential liabilities if they simply
ignored your letter and tossed it in the wastebasket.

