No one is every "fully" liable for your medical expenses.  An insurer
may be liable to the extent detailed in the policy.  A tortfeasor may
be liable for the results of the damages he causes.  But not for all of
your medical problems.

It is the right of the person responsible to have the actual amount
they owe reasonably determined.  If you don't give them access to any
of your medical information, that can't be done.

